<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>We believe that these are the top 3 best places to go skiing/snowboarding in Austria.<br/></p><p class="p--heading-1">1. St Anton</p><blockquote><p>“ By far the best freeriders resort in Austria and backed up by a world class village. It all comes at quite a price and the British invasian is leaving it less Austrian every ...”<br/></p></blockquote><p><img alt="" xlink:actuate="onLoad" xlink:show="embed" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../Pictures/St%20Anton.xml#data" cmexport:path="/Sites/Hybris%20Apparel/United%20States/English/Pictures/St%20Anton"/><br/></p><p class="p--heading-1">2. Ischgl</p><blockquote><p>“ Ischgl has plenty of good wide intermediate slopes, and hidden off-piste stashes. A super fast lift system, a season that lasts until May, great terrain park, and the most full on apres in the Alps, completes the ...”<br/></p></blockquote><p><img alt="" xlink:actuate="onLoad" xlink:show="embed" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../Pictures/Ischgl.xml#data" cmexport:path="/Sites/Hybris%20Apparel/United%20States/English/Pictures/Ischgl"/><br/></p><p class="p--heading-1">3. Solden</p><blockquote><p>“ Solden is one of Austria's best all round resorts, with some great intermediate terrain, and the craziest apres ski in the ...”<br/></p></blockquote><p><img alt="" xlink:actuate="onLoad" xlink:show="embed" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../Pictures/Solden.xml#data" cmexport:path="/Sites/Hybris%20Apparel/United%20States/English/Pictures/Solden"/><br/></p><p><br/></p></div></detailText>
